President Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with presidential aspirants on the platform of the All Progressive Congress. DAILY POST gathered that the meeting, which began at 9pm, also has in attendance the APC National Chairman, Abdullahi Adamu. Sources privy to the meeting disclosed that the agenda is centred around how the party stakeholders can arrive at a consensus ahead of the convention slated for June 6 and 8 in Abuja. Among those attending the meeting include the Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo, former Lagos State Governor, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, Kogi State Governor, Yahaya Bello, former Minister of Transport, Rotimi Amaechi, Chairman of the Nigerian Governors Forum, Kayode Fayemi, among others. More to comeâ€¦